Question: What is the eligibility criteria for application and admission into Undergraduate programs?
Answer: Applicants should have taken the Ethiopian Higher Education Qualifying Examination in the 2014, 2015, and 2016 Ethiopian Calendar years, fulfilling the passing points as set by the Ministry of Education. Applicants should take the undergraduate admission test (UAT) and score the minimum passing mark. Those who apply from overseas should process validation of their high school transcripts through the relevant authorities with the final assessment result by the Educational Training Authority (ETA).

metadata.question: What is the eligibility criteria for application and admission into Undergraduate programs?

pageContent:
Question: How can I get tuition fee support from the Government?
Answer: The current Government sponsorship scheme is from the Ministry of Education via cost-sharing. The cost-sharing scheme is limited to those with concrete evidence of a familyâ€™s economic deprivation or the lack of resources for a decent standard of living. Evidence should be provided from the Woreda of the Regional Administrative Units for regional students or from the Sub-City of Residence in Addis Ababa for residents of Addis Ababa.

metadata.question: How can I get tuition fee support from the Government?

pageContent:
Question: How many terms/semesters does the regular program have?
Answer: Most of the regular Undergraduate programs have two semesters per academic year; in Medicine and Dental Medicine programs, modular terms are available instead of semesters.

metadata.question: How many terms/semesters does the regular program have?

pageContent:
Question: How much is the application and UAT fee?
Answer: Application fee is ETB 375 and UAT fee is ETB 750.

metadata.question: How much is the application and UAT fee?

pageContent:
Question: How do I get my preferred field of study?
Answer: If you are a self-sponsored student, you will be allowed to choose four preferred programs and depending on your UAT and Ethiopian Higher Education Entrance Exam results, you will be tagged for one of the four preferred fields of study based on your eligibility. Please note that you can join one of your preferred fields of study only if you fulfill the eligibility criteria based on the above-mentioned exam results. If you are a Government-sponsored student, you will choose between the two broad fields of study. Nevertheless, the freshman courses will be offered to all the students in the same manner until the end of the first semester or the beginning of the second year for some fields. Please note that Health-related fields and the School of Law have additional assessments (written and oral exams) as part of their screening process. Please visit the program details described on the admission to programs portal for more description.

metadata.question: How do I get my preferred field of study?

pageContent:
Question: What is the eligibility criteria of application for remedial students?
Answer: If you have successfully completed remedial education in 2016 E.C and get a passing mark on the Exams, you are eligible to sit for the UAT. Once you pass the UAT and qualify for admission, you need to settle the cost-sharing payment of the public University you stayed at for the remedial courses.

metadata.question: What is the eligibility criteria of application for remedial students?

pageContent:
Question: Is the tuition payment per semester or monthly?
Answer: In most of the programs, tuition fees are paid in two installments per semester, making four installments per year. In Medicine and Dental Medicine programs, modular terms are available instead of semesters, thus yearly payments are practiced in two installments.

metadata.question: Is the tuition payment per semester or monthly?
